From: agent-os duckdb-pyodide build
Subject: [PATCH] CMakeLists.txt: skip GNU ld export flags under emscripten

wasm-ld doesn't support the GNU `--export-dynamic-symbol` linker flag;
pyodide-build handles symbol exports via `--exports=whole_archive`
instead. Add an emscripten branch before the generic UNIX branch so
the linker doesn't choke on an unrecognized flag.

Replicated from xlwings/duckdb-pyodide (scripts/patch_cmake.py — same
change, pre-applied as a patch in this recipe so the build flow stays
declarative).

---
 CMakeLists.txt | 4 ++++
 1 file changed, 4 insertions(+)

diff --git a/CMakeLists.txt b/CMakeLists.txt
--- a/CMakeLists.txt
+++ b/CMakeLists.txt
@@ -1,6 +1,10 @@
 if(APPLE)
   target_link_options(_duckdb PRIVATE "LINKER:-exported_symbol,_duckdb_adbc_init"
                                       "LINKER:-exported_symbol,_PyInit__duckdb")
+elseif(EMSCRIPTEN)
+  # wasm-ld does not support --export-dynamic-symbol; symbol exports are
+  # handled by pyodide-build via --exports=whole_archive
 elseif(UNIX AND NOT APPLE)
   target_link_options(
     _duckdb PRIVATE "LINKER:--export-dynamic-symbol=duckdb_adbc_init"
     "LINKER:--export-dynamic-symbol=PyInit__duckdb")
